This paper discusses the self-constructive nature of the brain and how it leads to the emergence of adaptive behavior. This topic is closely related to the fields of neural networks (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the principles of self-experimentation, self-growth, and self-repair, which are relevant to the field of control systems (cs.SY) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
